# Information (Information)
_arch_fast_install_banner_2

# ====================== ♥ Information! ======================

Continues execution of the script based on a scenario (script)'Arch Linux Fast Install LegasyBios (arch2018)'.
The initial software (packages) is installed, the necessary services are started, and data is written to configs (hhh.conf) for system configuration.
While the script is running) You will be prompted to perform the following actions:
Enter the user name( username), enter the computer name (hostname), and set the password for the user (username) and administrator (root). Configure the state of the hardware clock 'UTC or Localtime', but you can opt out and configure it already from the Arch system.
Questions will be asked: to install a particular utility (package), and on what hardware base the system will be installed (for installing Xorg 'usually called just X' and drivers) - Be Careful!
The point is that you make all the changes beforehand in the script itself and get the opportunity to quickly install the utilities (packages) that You have decided to install (provided That you have changed it for yourself, otherwise the script will install the software (packages) prescribed initially.
Don't worry the software (packages) are downloaded and installed from the 'Official Arch Linux repositories'. In any situation, the choice is always yours.

# ============================================================================

